{"parse":{"title":"John Hetherington","pageid":2932718,"revid":855516253,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For the mayor of Brisbane, see <a href=\"/wiki/John_Hetherington_(mayor)\" title=\"John Hetherington (mayor)\">John Hetherington (mayor)</a>.</div>\n<p>\n<b>John Hetherington</b> is a presumed apocryphal <a href=\"/wiki/English_people\" title=\"English people\">English</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Haberdasher\" title=\"Haberdasher\">haberdasher</a>, often credited as the inventor of the <a href=\"/wiki/Top_hat\" title=\"Top hat\">top hat</a>, which is said to have caused a riot when he first wore it in public on 15 January 1797.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#The_story\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The story</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Origin\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Origin</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Sources\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sources</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_story\">The story</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Hetherington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: The story\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The common form of the story, as reproduced in many books, has it that he was arraigned before the Lord Mayor on 15 January 1797 on a charge of <a href=\"/wiki/Breach_of_the_peace\" title=\"Breach of the peace\">breach of the peace</a> and inciting a riot, and was required to post a \u00a3500 bond. Reportedly he had \"appeared on the public highway wearing upon his head what he called a silk hat (which was shiny lustre and calculated to frighten timid people)\" and the officers of the Crown stated that \"several women fainted at the unusual sight, while children screamed, dogs yelped and a younger son of Cordwainer Thomas was thrown down by the crowd which collected and had his right arm broken\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Origin\">Origin</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Hetherington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Origin\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Evidently this story first appeared in a late 1890s edition of the <i>Hatters' Gazette</i>: in 1899 the quarterly journal <i><a href=\"/wiki/Notes_and_Queries\" title=\"Notes and Queries\">Notes and Queries</a></i> reported the story, noting that it originated in \"a recent number of the Hatters' Gazette\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Later accounts also attribute the story to the <i>Hatters' Gazette</i> \u2014 however, both the <i>Australian Law Review</i> of 1927, and <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Dearborn_Independent\" title=\"The Dearborn Independent\">The Dearborn Independent</a></i> in its \"I Read in the Papers\" column of 8 January 1927,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> erroneously describe it as being reported in a 1797 edition of the <i>Hatters' Gazette</i> (<i>The Dearborn Independent</i> specifying it more narrowly as the 16 January 1797 edition) \u2014 obviously an error, as the <i>Hatters' Gazette</i> only began publication in 1878.\n</p><p><i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Canberra_Times\" title=\"The Canberra Times\">The Canberra Times</a></i> for 10 June 1927 reproduced the usual account, with an introduction saying, \"During a discussion in the columns of 'The Times' (London) on the pioneer of umbrellas, a correspondent sent an extract from an old journal in her possession, dated 16 January 1797, giving the following amusing account of the wearing of the first silk hat in London\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> It is not known which \"old journal\" is referred to, but as noted above it cannot be the <i>Hatters' Gazette</i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Hetherington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Australian Law Review</i>, 1927, attributed to <i>Hatters' Gazette</i>, 16 January 1797</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Thornton, Richard H. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://nq.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/reprint/s9-III/70/325-b\">\"The First Silk Hat in London\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Notes_and_Queries\" title=\"Notes and Queries\">Notes and Queries</a></i> (s9-III): 325.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Notes+and+Queries&amp;rft.atitle=The+First+Silk+Hat+in+London&amp;rft.issue=s9-III&amp;rft.pages=325&amp;rft.aulast=Thornton&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+H.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnq.oxfordjournals.org%2Fcgi%2Freprint%2Fs9-III%2F70%2F325-b&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Hetherington\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Ford, Henry; W. J. Cameron (2003). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=nkZ2Il0aP5oC&amp;pg=PA30\"><i>Dearborn Independent Magazine January 1927-May 1927</i></a>. Kessinger Publishing. p.&#160;30. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-7661-5993-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-7661-5993-0\">0-7661-5993-0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Dearborn+Independent+Magazine+January+1927-May+1927&amp;rft.pages=30&amp;rft.pub=Kessinger+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.isbn=0-7661-5993-0&amp;rft.aulast=Ford&amp;rft.aufirst=Henry&amp;rft.au=W.+J.+Cameron&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DnkZ2Il0aP5oC%26pg%3DPA30&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Hetherington\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/1214155\">\"The First Top Hat\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Canberra_Times\" title=\"The Canberra Times\">The Canberra Times</a></i>. 10 June 1927.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Canberra+Times&amp;rft.atitle=The+First+Top+Hat&amp;rft.date=1927-06-10&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ftrove.nla.gov.au%2Fnewspaper%2Farticle%2F1214155&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Hetherington\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Hetherington&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/19981206040557/http://www.formalwear.org/public/resources/tophat.html\">Berendt, John. \"History of the Top Hat\". International Formalwear Association.</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.3ammagazine.com/3am/annus-horribilis/\">Jordinson, Sam. \"Annus Horribilis: A Chronicle of Comic Mishaps.\" John Murray.</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/london/4527223.stm\">BBC News \"<i>Changing the Flaws In London Laws</i>\"</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1345\nCached time: 20180909205423\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.136 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.177 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 340/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 5031/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 195/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 3300/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities load